        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 11 at 6:14PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 614 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Chappel Mill, or 9
miles north of Barnesville, moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Pea sized hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to exposed surfaces is possible.

Locations impacted include...
High Falls State Park, Liberty Hill, Goggins, Collier, Johnstonville,
Chappel Mill, and Forsyth.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.</instruction>
